As the name implies, they have tasty bagels with a vast choice of tasty cream cheeses. The bagels are larger than most other bagel shops. Seeds are on top only (some local places put the seeds on both sides which I like) however the bagels are very heavily seeded, which is awesome. Sandwiches are tasty and filling. Service is very quick and friendly enough. Fast AND friendly service don't always go together, but they seem to strike the right balance on most occasions. I never had an incorrect order so I've never had to truly test their customer service. I've also used them for catering and everything went smoothly. They don't accept credit cards except for catering.

A quick no-frills bagel shop in Bensonhurst that will hand roll you a bagel so tasty you'll forget you're so far from Manhattan. Crisp on the outside, warm and fluffy on the inside with a faint hint of a sourdough after taste lets you know these guys are serious about their dough. I personally like the eggs, provolone and tomato on a whole wheat everything bagel.  If you're in the area and have a hankering for a face stuffing bagel you will not regret your visit to Tasty Bagels.

Oh, so you are some hipster and your "slumming" in Bensonhurst and your belly is empty? Well, cupcake, you are not going to find some bagel store that uses flour from a village in Africa or anything like that fo fo BS that you are used to in Greenpoint. You are going to get your feed bag on at Tasty Bagels. They have been serving up great hand rolled bagels since before your dad opened your trust fund.  And if you are having a party, you will want them to cater it with their BIG WHEEL BAGEL.
